<bug>
    <id>91028</id>
    <title>LibreOffice 4.3.6.2 on Mac OS X Lion (10.7.5) says "You can update to 4.3.7" but LibreOffice 4.3.7 requires OS X 10.8 or later</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">I'm using LibreOffice 4.3.6.2 on Mac OS X Lion (10.7.5) on my old MacBook.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">Yesterday, my LibreOffice 4.3.6.2 says "You can update to LibreOffice 4.3.7".</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">I downloaded 4.3.7 and installed it, but it cannot work on my MacBook.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">And I knew 4.3.7 requires Mac OS X 10.8 or later.:-)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">I think it's a bug that LibreOffice 4.3.6.2 on Mac OS X Lion (10.7.5) says "You can update to 4.3.7", don't you?</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">I think checking update feature of LibreOffice should check between version of OS which it works on and requirement of new version, don't you?</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
